# TOCS Core Rules

## 1. Core Architecture

* TOCS is Formula First Architecture.
* Formula is the source of truth.
* Never create Deal, Order, Project, Pipeline, Transaction, Contract, SalesOrder, PurchaseOrder as top-level entities.
* Formula 1 = Item 1.
* Company has no fixed role.
* Role is determined only inside formula_participants.
* Company must remain a horizontal participant entity.
* Do not hard-code supplier, buyer, carrier, payer, receiver roles into Company.

## 2. Formula Rules

* Formula is the top-level business unit.
* All business flows must start from formula_id.
* KPI, dashboard, profit, receivable, payable, invoice, logistics, share, version, cancel, close must be derived from Formula.
* Do not create independent business roots outside Formula.
* Formula number must be generated by DB DEFAULT generate_formula_no().
* Never manually assign formula_no in application code, seed, API, or Prisma create input.

## 3. Version Trigger Policy

The following changes must never be handled by direct Formula update.

They must create:

1. formula_versions row
2. formula_calculation_snapshots row
3. audit_logs row

Version-triggering changes:

* `formulas.quantity`
* `formulas.contract_exchange_rate`
* `formulas.adjusted_exchange_rate`
* formula_participants record creation
* formula_participants record deletion
* `formula_participants.quantity`
* `formula_participants.buy_unit_price`
* `formula_participants.sell_unit_price`
* `formula_logistics.total_logistics_cost`
* `formula_shares.share_amount`
* `formula_shares.share_rate`

Any API input named `quantity`, `buyUnitPrice`, `sellUnitPrice`,
`contractExchangeRate`, `adjustedExchangeRate`, `logisticsCost`,
`totalLogisticsCost`, `shareAmount`, or `shareRate` must be routed to
VersionService unless explicitly documented as non-versioned metadata.

Formula update APIs must reject these fields and must not update them
directly.

Do not update these values through a normal Formula update API.

If Cursor is asked to implement Formula update, it must exclude all version-triggering fields.

Version not required:

* sequence_order
* role_group
* nature_group
* payment_group
* memo
* note
* content
* metadata-only fields

Note: formula_no is generated by DB Sequence + DEFAULT
(generate_formula_no()). version_no has NO Sequence and NO DEFAULT in
PostgreSQL. version_no must be calculated by Service layer
(MAX(version_no) + 1) and explicitly written on every INSERT. Never add
@default or autoincrement() to versionNo in schema.prisma.

## 4. Payment Rules

* Payment structure must support schedules and records.
* payment_schedules are planned amounts.
* payment_records are actual confirmed bank movements.
* Confirmed revenue is based on real bank deposits.
* Confirmed profit is based on real deposits and withdrawals.
* Do not calculate confirmed profit from expected formula values.
* Do not treat schedules as confirmed money.
* payment_records.is_canceled is separate from formulas.*_status = CANCELED.
* Do not mix payment record cancellation with Formula cancellation.
* Re-cancel attempt on an already-canceled payment record must return
  409 Conflict. Do not handle it idempotently.

## 5. Status Rules

* Status must not be auto-completed.
* Users manually complete or cancel status.
* Do not create code that automatically sets all statuses to COMPLETED.
* is_closed = TRUE means normal close only.
* CANCELED Formula is not the same as closed Formula.
* If formulas.is_closed = TRUE, reject direct modification of the original
  trade through normal update paths.
* Post-close settlement issue handling is allowed only through Settlement
  API or an explicit allowlist documented in API_SPEC §8.5 (DL-033).
  Do not infer allowance from general Formula, Payment, Invoice, Version, or
  Share update paths.

Closed Formula — forbidden through normal update paths:

* quantity, unit price, or exchange rate direct modification
* participant/company direct changes
* direct modification of existing calculation snapshots
* direct modification of existing payment record amounts
* direct manipulation of existing invoice amounts
* direct modification of existing share rules/amounts
* Version creation for trade-mutating purposes
* Share CRUD
* Formula general PATCH (content, note, unit)
* Formula cancel

Closed Formula — allowed through Settlement API / allowlist only (DL-033):

* additional payment record registration (append-only)
* payment record cancel then re-deposit (cancel + new record; no amount UPDATE)
* payment schedule append — Settlement API path only (not general 3.1)
* invoice status re-synchronization — update formulas.invoice_status only
  when derived_invoice_status = AMOUNT_MATCHED
* settlement memo/issue notes via audit_logs (action SETTLEMENT_NOTE)
* receivable/payable and confirmed KPI read paths

Still forbidden without explicit approval:

* Close undo
* Reopen (is_closed TRUE → FALSE)
* Adjustment Formula top-level entity implementation
* Cancel undo and close undo are not MVP features.
* Partial Formula cancellation is not MVP scope.

## 6. Invoice Rules

* Invoice is not a transaction blocker.
* Formula can continue before invoice completion.
* Formula cannot close without invoice completion.
* formulas.invoice_status is not automatically synchronized by DB trigger.
* API/Service layer must read v_formula_invoice_status and update formulas.invoice_status.
* Do not assume formula_invoices.status automatically updates formulas.invoice_status.
* When formulas.is_closed = TRUE, sync formulas.invoice_status only if
  derived_invoice_status = AMOUNT_MATCHED (DL-033). Skip formula column
  UPDATE otherwise to avoid chk_closed_requires_all_completed violation.

## 7. Share Rules

* formula_shares is the detail ledger for share rules.
* formula_calculation_snapshots.total_share is the calculated snapshot value.
* Share changes must create a new Version and new Snapshot.
* Do not directly update old snapshots to reflect share changes.
* Do not calculate expected_share directly from formula_participants.
* Share is not stored in formula_participants.

## 8. Prisma Rules

* PostgreSQL SQL files are the source of truth.
* Prisma is only an ORM mapping layer.
* Do not use Prisma Migrate.
* Never run or suggest:

  * prisma migrate dev
  * prisma migrate deploy
  * prisma db push
* Allowed Prisma commands:

  * prisma validate
  * prisma generate
  * prisma db pull only for read-only comparison when explicitly approved
* Do not modify DB schema from Prisma.
* Do not add tables, columns, indexes, constraints, triggers, or views through Prisma.
* schema.prisma must follow the existing PostgreSQL schema.
* Do not add GENERATED columns to Prisma models:

  * formula_participants.total_buy_amount
  * formula_participants.total_sell_amount
  * formula_invoices.total_amount
* Do not create Prisma models for DB Views.
* Views must be queried through repository-level raw SQL only.

## 9. Repository / Service / Action Rules

* Repository layer handles DB access only.
* Repository must not contain business policy.
* Service layer handles business rules, transactions, version creation policy, invoice synchronization, close/cancel rules.
* Action/API layer handles request parsing, response formatting, and user-facing errors.
* Action must not call Prisma directly.
* Action must call Service.
* Service may call Repository.
* Repository may call Prisma.

Allowed structure:

Action -> Service -> Repository -> Prisma -> PostgreSQL

Forbidden structure:

Action -> Prisma
Action -> Repository
Repository -> Service
Repository -> business decision

## 10. DB Responsibility vs API Responsibility

DB is responsible for:

* CHECK constraints
* Triggers
* GENERATED columns
* Partial indexes
* Composite FK validation
* Formula number generation
* Amount verified trigger calculation

API/Service is responsible for:

* formula_no never manually assigned
* invoice_status synchronization (with closed-formula conditional sync per DL-033)
* share change creating new Version
* closed formula trade-mutation guard on Version, Share, Participant, Formula PATCH
* closed formula settlement allowlist: payment record append/cancel,
  settlement payment-schedule, settlement audit note
* version_no conflict retry: exactly 1 retry with re-fetch of
  MAX(version_no), then return an explicit "concurrent edit conflict"
  message. Do not implement multi-retry or exponential backoff
  (V2 scope).
* close pre-check using v_formula_closeable
* user-friendly error messages
* cancel transaction grouping: 6 status field UPDATE + 6
  formula_status_logs INSERT + 1 audit_logs INSERT must be wrapped in a
  single transaction.
* audit log creation where required
* status log creation where required

Do not duplicate DB constraints in application logic unless it is only for user-friendly pre-check.

## 11. View Rules

* v_formula_confirmed_kpi is for confirmed cash-based KPI.
* v_formula_profit_engine is for expected profit engine and latest snapshot.
* v_formula_invoice_status is for invoice derived status.
* v_formula_closeable is for close eligibility.
* v_payment_unmatched is for unmatched payment records.
* v_participant_confirmed_kpi is for participant-level confirmed KPI.
* These Views intentionally do NOT filter formulas.*_status = CANCELED.
  Confirmed cash movements remain visible even after cancellation. This
  is NOT a bug. Excluding canceled Formulas from dashboards/reports is
  Application/UI responsibility, never a View modification.
* Do not recreate View logic in TypeScript if the View already exists.
* Use raw SQL repository methods for Views.

## 12. MVP Scope Control

Do not add postponed V1/V2 features unless explicitly approved.

Do not add these without approval:

* approval workflow
* permission matrix
* notification system
* AI analysis
* forecasting
* file upload
* external ERP integration
* bank API integration
* advanced concurrency manager
* undo close
* reopen (is_closed TRUE → FALSE)
* adjustment formula entity
* undo cancel
* partial cancel
* participant order swap API
* dashboard extras beyond MVP KPI

## 13. Naming Protection

Do not introduce these top-level entities:

* Deal
* Order
* Project
* Pipeline
* Transaction
* Contract
* SalesOrder
* PurchaseOrder

Use Formula instead.

Do not rename Formula to another business concept.

## 14. UI/UX Workflow (v0 + Cursor)

Product UI uses a two-tool pipeline. Backend, DB, and API stay frozen during UI iteration unless explicitly approved.

### v0

* UI/UX 시안 및 프론트엔드 컴포넌트 **초안** 생성 담당.
* GitHub 연동 → **`web/**` 기준**으로 작업.
* Premium SaaS visual direction 반영 (§16).
* Mock data 기반 시안 생성 — API 연결 금지.

### Cursor

* v0 생성 코드를 TOCS 구조에 맞게 **정리·통합** — 무조건 그대로 덮어쓰지 말 것.
* **`web/**` 내부에서만** 리팩토링.
* `AppShell`, `CompanyProvider`, `DateRangeProvider` 유지 또는 정합성 맞춰 통합.
* Backend / API / DB / Prisma 수정 **금지** — 필요 시 즉시 중단·보고.
* Formula First / Company Context / Profit Engine (Estimated ≠ Realized) 위반 여부 **먼저 점검**.
* `cd web && npm run typecheck` · lint/build 가능 시 실행; root `npm run typecheck` · `npm run test:integration` 검증 담당.
* UI 개선은 작은 단위로 커밋 가능하게 분리.

